{
  "id": "L3",
  "title": "At the Supermarket",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Welcome! In this lesson, you'll learn how to ask for help at a Spanish supermarket, 'el supermercado'."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V01",
      "data": {
        "El supermercado": "The supermarket"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Perdón",
        "meaning": "Excuse me"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "¿Dónde está...?",
        "meaning": "Where is...?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "In Spanish, all nouns have a gender. Use 'el' for masculine words and 'la' for feminine words."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V02",
      "data": {
        "La leche": "The milk"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V03",
      "data": {
        "El pan": "The bread"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V04",
      "data": {
        "Allí": "There"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L3_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "Leche",
        "phonetic": "[ˈle.tʃe]",
        "tip": "The 'ch' in Spanish sounds just like the 'ch' in the English word 'cheese'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L3_S01",
      "title": "Asking for Help",
      "setting": "You are in a supermarket and can't find some items. You see an employee and approach them for help.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Get the employee's attention",
          "chatbot_message": ""
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask where the milk is",
          "chatbot_message": "¡Hola! ¿Sí?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask where the bread is",
          "chatbot_message": "La leche está allí"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Great! The employee is helping you. Now let's learn how to ask for quantities and special prices."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Quiero...",
        "meaning": "I want..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V05",
      "data": {
        "Quinientos gramos": "500 grams"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V06",
      "data": {
        "De": "Of"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V07",
      "data": {
        "Las uvas": "The grapes"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V08",
      "data": {
        "El queso": "The cheese"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "¿Está en oferta?",
        "meaning": "Is it on sale?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L3_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "Queso",
        "phonetic": "[ˈke.so]",
        "tip": "The 'que' here sounds like 'keh'. The 'u' is silent."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Gracias",
        "meaning": "Thank you"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "De nada",
        "meaning": "You're welcome"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L3_S02",
      "title": "Asking about Products",
      "setting": "The employee has shown you the bread. Now you see some grapes and cheese nearby.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Ask for 500 grams of grapes",
          "chatbot_message": "El pan está aquí. ¿Algo más?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask if the cheese is on sale",
          "chatbot_message": "Aquí tiene"
        },
        {
          "title": "Thank the employee",
          "chatbot_message": "Sí, el queso está en oferta"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Excellent! You have all your items. Let's go to the checkout ('la caja') to pay."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V09",
      "data": {
        "La caja": "The checkout"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Buenas tardes",
        "meaning": "Good afternoon"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V10",
      "data": {
        "Una bolsa": "A bag"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V11",
      "data": {
        "Por favor": "Please"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "A simple way to ask for something is to say the item followed by 'por favor', like 'Una bolsa, por favor'."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Son diez euros",
        "meaning": "It's ten euros"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V12",
      "data": {
        "Vale": "OK"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E09",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Adiós",
        "meaning": "Goodbye"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L3_S03",
      "title": "Paying at the Checkout",
      "setting": "You've placed your items on the counter and are now interacting with the cashier.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Greet the cashier",
          "chatbot_message": "Buenas tardes"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask for a bag",
          "chatbot_message": ""
        },
        {
          "title": "Respond to the total",
          "chatbot_message": "Claro. Son diez euros"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}